  "model_paragraph": "The flowchart shows how PET bottles are recycled. Overall, this is a fairly simple process with six steps, running from the consumer through processing and back to the consumer. First, bottles are collected and transported by lorry to warehouses, where they are stored. Next, they are inspected and sorted by size and colour before being sent on for further processing. The plastic is then chopped up into small pieces and scrubbed clean. Finally, the flakes are packed into boxes, made into new products and resold.",
